## Review Notes (for App Store Review team)

**What the app does:**
DreamLens is an AI-powered dream journal and interpreter. Users type a description of their dream, and the app uses an on-device AI language model to generate an interpretation including emotional tone, key symbols, a written analysis, and a color-based "dream aura" visualization.

**How the AI works:**
The app bundles a quantized open-source AI language model (Qwen 3.5-0.8B, Q4_K_M quantization, GGUF format, ~533 MB). This model runs entirely on-device using the llama.cpp inference engine via a Swift wrapper library (swift-llama-cpp). The model uses the device's GPU (Metal) for acceleration.

No internet connection is required. No API calls are made. No data is sent to any server. The AI model is included in the app bundle and loaded into memory when the user first requests a dream interpretation.

**How to test:**
1. Launch the app — you will see a splash screen with the DreamLens logo, then the home screen.
2. Tap the purple "+" button in the bottom-right corner to create a new dream entry.
3. Type any dream description in the text field. Example: "I was flying over a green forest and saw a river below me. Then I landed on a mountain and found a golden key."
4. Tap "Decode Dream" and wait approximately 10-30 seconds for the on-device AI to generate the interpretation (time varies by device; newer devices are faster).
5. The result screen will display: emotional tone with emoji, dream symbols with meanings, a written interpretation, and an animated dream aura.
6. Dismiss the result — the dream is automatically saved to the journal on the home screen.
7. Tap any saved dream card to revisit its interpretation.
8. Long-press a dream card to delete it.
9. Tap the gear icon (top-right) to access Settings where you can change the AI response language (English/Russian) and interpretation style (Mystical/Scientific/Poetic).

**Important technical notes for review:**
- The app binary is large (~600 MB) because the AI model file (~533 MB) is bundled inside the app. This is intentional — it enables fully offline operation.
- The app uses the `com.apple.developer.kernel.increased-memory-limit` entitlement because loading the AI model into RAM requires additional memory. This is a standard entitlement for on-device ML applications.
- First interpretation after launch may take slightly longer (~5-10 seconds extra) as the model loads into memory. Subsequent interpretations are faster.
- The app requires iPhone 12 (A14 Bionic) or newer for adequate AI inference performance.
- No internet permission is requested or used. The app has no URL schemes, no deep links, no web views, and makes no network calls.

**Third-party dependencies:**
- swift-llama-cpp (MIT License): A Swift wrapper around llama.cpp for on-device LLM inference. Source included in the project as a local package.
- llama.cpp (MIT License): Open-source C/C++ library for running large language models. Distributed as an XCFramework binary, downloaded during the Swift Package Manager build process.

**AI model details:**
- Model: Qwen 3.5-0.8B (open-source, Apache 2.0 License, by Alibaba Cloud)
- Quantization: Q4_K_M (4-bit quantized for mobile efficiency)
- Format: GGUF
- Source: Hugging Face (unsloth/Qwen3.5-0.8B-GGUF)
- The model generates creative dream interpretations. It does not provide medical, psychological, or therapeutic advice.
